21/05/2003
CRETE, Greece -- EU police chiefs wrapped up a two-day meeting on the island of Crete Tuesday (20 May). Participants discussed the need for closer co-operation in fighting terrorism, illegal immigration, organised crime and forgery. They also pledged to help Greece with security during the 2004 Olympics and to develop a system for collaborating in trans-national police operations. (ANA- 20/05/03)
